---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';

const listingURL = 'https://theabacoclub.com/rentals/cabana-112/';

const structuredData = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "TravelAction",
  "name": "Visiting Abaco, Bahamas — Local Area Guide",
  "description": "A practical guide to Marsh Harbour and the Abacos for visitors staying at Cabana 112, The Abaco Club on Winding Bay.",
  "location": {
    "@type": "Place",
    "name": "Marsh Harbour, Abaco, Bahamas",
    "address": {
      "@type": "PostalAddress",
      "addressLocality": "Marsh Harbour",
      "addressRegion": "Abaco",
      "addressCountry": "BS"
    }
  }
};
---

<Base
  title="Abaco Area Guide for Cabana Guests"
  description="A practical local guide to Abaco, Bahamas — getting here, getting around, what to do, and what's close to Cabana 112 at The Abaco Club on Winding Bay."
  canonicalURL="/local-area/"
  structuredData={structuredData}
>
  <style>
    .guide-header {
      background: var(--navy);
      color: #fff;
      padding: 3.5rem 1.5rem;
      text-align: center;
    }

    .guide-header .eyebrow {
      font-family: sans-serif;
      font-size: 0.75rem;
      letter-spacing: 0.18em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: var(--coral);
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
    }

    .guide-header h1 {
      font-size: clamp(1.6rem, 4vw, 2.4rem);
      font-weight: 400;
      max-width: 600px;
      margin: 0 auto 1rem;
      line-height: 1.25;
      letter-spacing: 0.02em;
    }

    .guide-header p {
      font-family: sans-serif;
      font-size: 0.92rem;
      color: rgba(255,255,255,0.7);
      max-width: 520px;
      margin: 0 auto;
      line-height: 1.7;
    }

    .guide-body {
      max-width: var(--max-w);
      margin: 0 auto;
      padding: 3rem 1.5rem 4rem;
    }

    .guide-body section { margin-bottom: 3rem; }

    .guide-body h2 {
      font-size: 1.4rem;
      font-weight: 400;
      color: var(--navy);
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
      padding-bottom: 0.5rem;
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
      letter-spacing: 0.02em;
    }

    .guide-body p {
      font-family: sans-serif;
      font-size: 0.92rem;
      color: var(--muted);
      line-height: 1.85;
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
    }

    .guide-body ul {
      padding-left: 1.25rem;
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
    }

    .guide-body li {
      font-family: sans-serif;
      font-size: 0.92rem;
      color: var(--muted);
      line-height: 1.7;
      margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
    }

    .info-box {
      background: #f8f4f0;
      border-left: 3px solid var(--teal);
      padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;
      margin: 1.5rem 0;
    }

    .info-box p { margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
    .info-box p:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }

    .booking-section {
      text-align: center;
      padding: 3rem 1.5rem;
      background: var(--navy);
      color: #fff;
    }

    .booking-section h2 {
      font-size: 1.5rem;
      font-weight: 400;
      margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    }

    .booking-section p {
      font-family: sans-serif;
      font-size: 0.9rem;
      color: rgba(255,255,255,0.7);
      max-width: 500px;
      margin: 0 auto 1.5rem;
      line-height: 1.7;
    }

    .booking-section a {
      display: inline-block;
      background: var(--coral);
      color: #fff;
      text-decoration: none;
      padding: 0.85rem 2rem;
      font-family: sans-serif;
      font-size: 0.88rem;
      font-weight: 600;
      letter-spacing: 0.08em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
    }

    .booking-section a:hover { background: #e0705f; color: #fff; }
  </style>

  <div class="guide-header">
    <p class="eyebrow">Abaco, Bahamas</p>
    <h1>Practical Guide for Visitors to Winding Bay</h1>
    <p>
      Getting here, getting around, what to do on and off the property —
      written for guests staying at Cabana 112 at The Abaco Club.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="guide-body">

    <section>
      <h2>Getting to Abaco</h2>
      <p>
        Abaco is one of the most accessible Out Islands in the Bahamas. The main gateway is
        <strong>Leonard M. Thompson International Airport (MHH)</strong> in Marsh Harbour.
      </p>
      <p>There are several ways to get there:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Direct charter from the US East Coast</strong> — the fastest option from Florida, the Carolinas, or Georgia. Many guests fly private directly to MHH.</li>
        <li><strong>Commercial via Nassau (NAS)</strong> — Bahamasair and other carriers connect Nassau to Marsh Harbour on short daily flights (about 45 minutes).</li>
        <li><strong>Via Freeport (FPO)</strong> — another connection point, though less frequent than Nassau.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        From Marsh Harbour airport, The Abaco Club is roughly a 20-minute drive south toward
        Cherokee Sound. The club can often arrange transport — it's worth asking when you confirm
        your reservation through the official listing.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Getting around once you're here</h2>
      <p>
        Within the property, a golf cart is the standard mode of transport — and genuinely the
        right one. The Abaco Club's grounds cover a meaningful area, and a cart makes moving
        between the cabana, the beach, the clubhouse, and the golf shop effortless.
      </p>
      <p>
        For leaving the property, a rental car from Marsh Harbour gives you the most flexibility.
        The main town has grocery stores, a few hardware shops, and several marinas. The roads
        on Great Abaco are paved and easy to navigate — Bahamians drive on the left.
      </p>
      <div class="info-box">
        <p><strong>Practical note:</strong> Abaco had significant recovery work following Hurricane Dorian in 2019. Marsh Harbour has rebuilt substantially, but infrastructure and service availability can differ from what you might expect of a larger tourist destination. Plan ahead for groceries and supplies.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>On the property</h2>
      <p>
        Cabana 112 is positioned on the first fairway, which puts you close to most of the
        club's core amenities:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Winding Bay Beach</strong> — a short walk through the grounds. Two miles of private white-sand beach, calm water, consistent trade winds in the afternoon.</li>
        <li><strong>Flipper's Beach Bar</strong> — right at the beach access, serving drinks and food throughout the day. Informal, relaxed, exactly what a beach bar should be.</li>
        <li><strong>Golf</strong> — The Abaco Club's course is ranked #1 in the Bahamas. The first tee is visible from the cabana's sunroom window.</li>
        <li><strong>Tennis and pickleball</strong> — courts are available to guests. Equipment is typically available at the golf shop.</li>
        <li><strong>Clubhouse and dining</strong> — the main clubhouse has formal and informal dining options. Hours and reservations are handled through the club directly.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Best time of year to visit</h2>
      <p>
        Peak season runs from mid-December through April, when temperatures are in the low 80s,
        humidity is lower than the summer months, and the trade winds are reliable. This is when
        the club is most active and social.
      </p>
      <p>
        May through early July is a secondary sweet spot — water temperatures rise, crowds thin,
        and rates at most properties reflect the shoulder season. Late summer through October is
        hurricane season; many guests avoid it, though storms are far from guaranteed.
      </p>
      <p>
        January and February tend to offer the clearest water conditions at Winding Bay — worth
        knowing if beach snorkeling is a priority.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Beyond the property</h2>
      <p>
        The Abacos are a boating destination first. If you have access to a boat (or can charter one),
        the sea of Abaco is dotted with small cays — Elbow Cay with Hope Town, Great Guana Cay,
        Man-O-War Cay — each with its own character. Day trips by water are easy.
      </p>
      <p>
        Hope Town on Elbow Cay is particularly well-known: a small, pastel-painted settlement
        with a historic candy-striped lighthouse that's still hand-operated. The 45-minute ferry
        from Marsh Harbour takes you there directly.
      </p>
    </section>

  </div>

  <div class="booking-section">
    <h2>Ready to book?</h2>
    <p>
      Cabana 112 is available to rent exclusively through The Abaco Club's reservation system.
      Bookings are open to members of the Southworth portfolio of clubs.
    </p>
    <a href={listingURL} target="_blank" rel="noopener">
      View Cabana 112 at The Abaco Club →
    </a>
  </div>
</Base>
